summary: This document is an email chain from November 2019 among U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USAO SDNY) prosecutors, discussing scheduling a meeting to catch up on the Epstein case. It mentions a recent interview in California that did not yield significant new information for an enticement charge and notes an upcoming limited proffer session with a witness.

events.title: California Interview
events.description: Prosecutors conducted an interview in California with a potential victim/witness. The meeting did not add significant information, and an enticement charge was deemed unlikely based on timing/location facts. The individual was unsure about pursuing a criminal case.

events.title: Upcoming Limited Proffer
events.description: A witness (referred to as 'she') is scheduled to come in for a limited proffer session to discuss her background.

keyFacts: Prosecutors from the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York were actively discussing the Epstein case in November 2019.
An interview in California with a potential victim did not yield significant new information for an enticement charge due to timing and location facts.
The individual from the California interview was still undecided about pursuing a criminal case, with plans to circle back with her attorneys later in November 2019.
A witness was scheduled for a limited proffer session to discuss her background a week from the email date (targeting November 26, 2019).
The email chain shows internal coordination among prosecutors, with references to working on a 'pile of memos' related to the case.
